  "texts": [
    "The current work relied on GPT-4, a stateof-the-art LLM released by OpenAI.",
    "As noted in the Methods section, one limitation of GPT-4 (along with other Ope-nAI models) is that the details of its architecture or training data have not been made public.",
    "Further, after pre-training, GPT-4 was trained using \"reinforcement learning with human feedback (RLHF), in which model weights are iteratively updated according to explicit human feedback about which model outputs are appropriate or inappropriate; the details of this feedback are also not entirely open.",
    "Lack of model transparency could be a concern for many scientific questions about LLM performance.",
    "For example, if one is interested in how exposure specific kinds (or amounts) of linguistic input facilitates performance on a task, then not knowing exactly what a model is trained on impedes one's ability to make relevant scientific inferences."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}